#: ../../G/Gang-of-Four.rst:5
msgid "Gang of Four"
msgstr "Gang of Four"

#: ../../G/Gang-of-Four.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../G/Gang-of-Four.rst:9
msgid ""
"(also abbreviated GOF) [prob. a play on the ‘Gang Of Four’ who briefly ran "
"Communist China after the death of Mao] Describes either the authors or the "
"book *Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software* "
"published in 1995 by Addison-Wesley (ISBN 0-201-63361-2). The authors "
"forming the Gang Of Four are Erich Gamma, Richard Helm, Ralph Johnson and "
"John Vlissides. They are also sometimes referred to as ‘Gamma et. al.’ The "
"authors state at `http://www.hillside.net/patterns/DPBook/GOF.html "
"<http://www.hillside.net/patterns/DPBook/GOF.html>`_\\  \"Why are we ... "
"called this? Who knows. Somehow the name just stuck.\" The term is also used"
" to describe any of the design patterns that are used in the book, referring"
" to the patterns within it as ‘Gang Of Four Patterns.’"
msgstr ""
"(GOFとも略される)[おそらく毛沢東の死後、短期間中国共産党を運営した‘四人組(Gang Of Four)’にかけたもの] "
"1995年にAddison-Wesleyから出版された書籍 *Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-"
"Oriented Software* (ISBN 0-201-63361-2)、またはその著者たちを指す。Gang Of "
"Fourを構成する著者は、Erich Gamma、Richard Helm、Ralph Johnson、John "
"Vlissidesである。彼らは‘Gamma et. al.’と呼ばれることもある。著者たちは "
"`http://www.hillside.net/patterns/DPBook/GOF.html "
"<http://www.hillside.net/patterns/DPBook/GOF.html>`_\\  "
"で「なぜ我々は…こう呼ばれているのか?さあね。なぜかこの名前が定着しただけだ」と述べている。この用語は、本の中で使われているデザインパターンのいずれかを表すのにも使われ、本の中のパターンを‘Gang"
" Of Fourパターン’と呼ぶ。"
